South Africa Records Monthly Budget Surplus of 12.6 Billion Rand in June

-- B y   G o r d o n   B e l l
-- 
2011-07-29T12:17:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-29/south-africa-records-monthly-budget-surplus-of-12-6-billion-rand-in-june.html
South Africa  posted a budget surplus
of 12.6 billion rand ($145 million) in June, compared with
surplus of 8.9 billion rand in the same month a year earlier,
the National Treasury said.  Tax revenue increased 10 percent to 82.2 billion rand from
a year earlier, while expenditure rose 6 percent to 69.6 billion
rand, the Pretoria-based Treasury said on its website today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Gordon Bell  at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  